707103f-b.title: Brooklyn: Ave. U - 29th St. E.
707103f-b.text:
(1)
29O01-2919 Ave. U.. north side, between East 29th Street and Nos-
trand Ave., show ing the home of Capt. Luts (No. 2919) in the foreground,
who was an ex-police captain.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing the same house known also as Fort Lutz, Note
the cannons, relics of the Civil War, which were made in 1862 and weigh
each 816 1bs.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, at the N.W. corner of Nostrand Ave., showing the Nostrand
Ave. trolley at its terminal.
February 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
